               <p>652. 
               
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-defend2120" type="defendantName">
                     CATHERINE 
                     RAGAN
                  <interp inst="t18310217-226-defend2120" type="surname" value="RAGAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-defend2120" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-defend2120" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-defend2120" type="age" value="32"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18310217-226-off1326" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-off1326" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-off1326" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310217-226-cd1327" type="crimeDate">16th of February</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-226-off1326 t18310217-226-cd1327"></join>, 1 half-sovereign
            </rs>, the money of 
               
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-victim2122" type="victimName">
                     Thomas 
                     Kirby
                  <interp inst="t18310217-226-victim2122" type="surname" value="Kirby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-victim2122" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-victim2122" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-226-off1326 t18310217-226-victim2122"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS KIRBY. I am a <rs id="t18310217-226-viclabel1328" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-226-victim2122 t18310217-226-viclabel1328"></join>, and lodge at the Dundee Arms, in Wapping. On the evening of the 16th of February I saw the prisoner, who asked if I would purchase any oysters - she said she had a large family, and I said I had no objection to buy her some beef-steaks for her family; we went to a shop - I ordered some for her, and was going to pay for them; I had a half-sovereign and some silver in my watch-fob, in a bit of paper - I opened the paper, and some of it fell; the butcher said I had dropped something, and he was confident by the chink of it that it was gold - I begged for a light; the prisoner stooped down, and took up a sixpence, which she was very willing to give me, but she was seen to take up the half-sovereign, and I gave charge of her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. When I first met him in a public-house he made me take a couple of glasses of liquor, which I am not accustomed to; I do not know whether I took it up or not. Witness. I had not been in any public-house with her - she complained of poverty, and said she had nine children; I had made a pretty good voyage, and thought I would relieve her.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183102170130"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-person2123">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SAUNDERS
               <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2123" type="surname" value="SAUNDERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2123" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2123" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a butcher, and live in <placeName id="t18310217-226-crimeloc1329">Old Gravel-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-226-crimeloc1329" type="placeName" value="Old Gravel-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-226-crimeloc1329" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-226-off1326 t18310217-226-crimeloc1329"></join>. The prisoner and the prosecutor came to my shop on the 16th of February, to buy a bit of beef - he was going to pay, and some money fell down on the pavement; the prisoner stooped, and appeared to me to pick up something, and put into her pocket - she stooped again, and picked up a sixpence, which she gave the prosecutor; I thought, by the sound, that a half-sovereign had dropped.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-person2124">
                  JOHN 
                  EASTERBROOK
               <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2124" type="surname" value="EASTERBROOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2124" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-serjeant. I was in the inner-room at the watch-house while the prisoner was in the outer room; I went into the outer room, and as I went in the prisoner moved - I heard something fall; I looked, and saw a half-sovereign on the floor, by her feet; I said, "I thought you said you had not had it;" she said she had never seen it, nor touched it - she appeared sober before, but appeared very drunk when I found it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-person2125">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SAUNDERS
               <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2125" type="surname" value="SAUNDERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2125" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . She appeared sober when I saw her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He made me drink four glasses of liquor, and put a pipe into my mouth to smoke, which was found in my pocket - he said he would be better to me than my husband.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-person2126">
                  THOMAS 
                  KIRBY
               <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2126" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2126" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2126" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . It is no such thing - I was not half an hour with her; I was in no house with her, and did not give her any thing to drink.</p>
               <p>JURY. Q. Did you ask where she lived? A. No, but she said she had a family - I never saw her before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-226-person2127">
                  RICHARD 
                  PARKHURST
               <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2127" type="surname" value="PARKHURST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2127" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-person2127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I took the prisoner to the watch-house - I found 3s. 6d. on her; I afterwards heard the half-sovereign fall from her clothes, and saw it picked up.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310217-226-verdict1330" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-verdict1330" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 32. - <rs id="t18310217-226-punish1331" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310217-226-punish1331" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-226-defend2120 t18310217-226-punish1331"></join>
               Confined One Week
            </rs>.</p>
